01160                 //Remove Dependency Table Elements (BR,MEM,REG)

01162                 //Reset Register Renaming Table
01163                 if (!perfectRegRen && coreType != IN_ORDER) {
01164                         iROB->Nth(i)->squashRenameReg(GRF);

01166                 if (coreType == PHRASEBLOCK) {

01168                                 iROB->Nth(i)->delDepTableEntris_LRF(LRFTables[k], coreType, perfectRegRen);
01169                         }
01170                 }
01171                 getSquashRFstatForStatus(iROB->Nth(i), iROB->Nth(i)->getStatus());
01172                 getSquashRFstat(iROB->Nth(i));
01173                 if (iROB->Nth(i)->getType() == BR) squashBRinsCount++;
01174                 if (insID == iROB->Nth(i)->getInsID()) break;
01175                 //ATTENTION: Don't add code here
01176         }
01177         //Flush LSQ
01178         if (memoryModel == NAIVE_SPECUL) {
01179                 squashLQinsCount += oooLD_squashLQ (loadStoreQue, insID);

01183         //Remove Instruction from ROB
01184         removeFromiWindow(insID);
01185         removeFromiResStn (insID);

01783         //At SQUASH, wait for ROB to drain
01784         if (isSquashed && iROB->NumElements() > 0) {return 0;}

01790                 depTables->flush_depTables();
01791         }
01792         //Fill ICQ
01793         if (!eof) addToInsCache(cycle);
01794         //int activeWinRange = iROB->NumElements() - iWinPointer;
01795         if (iROB->NumElements() < ROBsize) {
01796                 int diff = ROBsize - iROB->NumElements();

01805                                 break;
01806                         } else if (result == -2) {
01807                                 popFromInsCache();
01808                                 delete newIns;

02215                         if (debug) printf("WARNING: Unrecognized Instruction. Skipping (%s)\n", cTemp);

02220         return 0; //Successful completion (TODO: fix return values)

02717 bool checkAncestor(instruction* ins, int bottom, int top, List<instruction*> *iWindow) {
02718         if (ins->isGotoSideBuff() == true) return false;
02719         for (int i = 0; i < ins->getNumAncestors(); i++) {

02721                 for (int j = bottom; j < top; j++) {

02723                             iWindow->Nth(j)->isGotoSideBuff() == false &&
02724                             iWindow->Nth(j)->getInsID() == ancestor->getInsID()) {
02725                                 return false; //ins cannot be moved due to dependency
02726                         }

02819 /* MEMORY ADDRESS DEPENDENCY CHECK */
02820 bool checkMemDependency (int indx) {
02821         if (iROB->Nth(indx)->getMemType() == READ) { //RAW Hazard Check (word level address check)
02822                 for (int i = indx-1; i >= 0; i--) {
02823                         if (iROB->Nth(i)->getMemType() == WRITE && iROB->Nth(i)->getStatus() != complete) {
02824                                 long int temp1 = iROB->Nth(i)->getMemAddr() >> WORD_OFFSET;
02825                                 long int temp2 = iROB->Nth(indx)->getMemAddr() >> WORD_OFFSET;
02826                                 if (temp1 == temp2) {
02827                                         return true; //found true dependency (RAW)
02828                                 }
02829                         }
02830                 }
02831         } else if (iROB->Nth(indx)->getMemType() == WRITE) { //WAR Hazard Check (cache line level addr check)
02832                 for (int i = indx-1; i >= 0; i--) {
02833                         if ((iROB->Nth(i))->getMemType() == WRITE && (iROB->Nth(i))->getStatus() != complete) {
02834                                 return true; //Memory store total ordering (WAW)
02835                         } else if (iROB->Nth(i)->getMemType() == READ && iROB->Nth(i)->getStatus() != complete) {
02836                                 //WAR hazard check
02837                                 long int temp1 = iROB->Nth(i)->getMemAddr()    >> (WORD_OFFSET+BLOCK_OFFSET);
02838                                 long int temp2 = iROB->Nth(indx)->getMemAddr() >> (WORD_OFFSET+BLOCK_OFFSET);
02839                                 if (temp1 == temp2) {
02840                                         return true; //found false dependency (WAR)
02841                                 }
02842                         }
02843                 }
02844         }
02845         return false;
02846 }

02848 void recordMemAccess(instruction *_ins, int lat) {
02849         int totCount = 0;
02850         int missCount = 0;
02851         long int insAddr = _ins->getInsAddr();
02852         Assert(insAddr > 0);
02853 
02854         //Keep track of total number of accesses
02855         if (memRdTotCountTable.count(insAddr) > 0) {
02856                 totCount = memRdTotCountTable.find(insAddr)->second;
02857                 memRdTotCountTable.erase(insAddr);
02858         }
02859         totCount++;
02860         memRdTotCountTable.insert(pair<long int,int>(insAddr,totCount));
02861 
02862 
02863         //Keep track of total number of misses
02864         //If an ins never misses, it will not be in this list
02865         if (lat > cacheLat[0]) {
02866                 if (memRdMissCountTable.count(insAddr) > 0) {
02867                         missCount = memRdMissCountTable.find(insAddr)->second;
02868                         memRdMissCountTable.erase(insAddr);
02869                         missCount++;
02870                         memRdMissCountTable.insert(pair<long int,int>(insAddr,missCount));
02871                 } else {
02872                         missCount = 1;
02873                         memRdMissCountTable.insert(pair<long int,int>(insAddr,missCount));
02874                 }
02875         }
02876         Assert(totCount > 0 && missCount >= 0);
02877 }

03177                                 aluFreeTime[j] = cycle+1;//non-blocking LD/ST

03191                                         printf("\n");
03192                                 }
03193                                 /*-----STAT-----*/

03195                         } else if (iResStation->NumElements() > 0 && 
03196                                   (iResStation->Nth(0)->getType() == ALU ||

03503 /***************************************
03504  * STRAND Core implementation
03505  ***************************************/
03506 long long int total_num_strand_ins = 0;
03507 long long int dyn_num_strands = 0;
03508 void createStrand(instruction *ins, int indx, int iWinIndx, List<instruction*> *iWindow) {
03509         bool foundIns = false;
03510         bool strand_formed = false;
03511         instruction *prevIns = ins;
03512         if (ins->getDependents()->NumElements() != 1)
03513                 return;
03514         do {
03515                 foundIns = false;
03516                 prevIns = ins;
03517                 ins = ins->getDependents()->Nth(0);
03518                 if (!(ins->getDependents()->NumElements() == 1 && 
03519                       ins->getNumAncestors() == 1 && 
03520                           ins->getNthAncestor(0)->getInsID() == prevIns->getInsID()))// &&
03521                           //upldMissRateProfileMap.find(ins->getInsAddr()) ==  upldMissRateProfileMap.end()))
03522                           //ins->getType() != MEM))
03523                         break;
03524                 for (int i = iWinIndx; i < iWindow->NumElements(); i++) {
03525                         if (ins->getInsID() == iWindow->Nth(i)->getInsID()) {
03526                                 foundIns = true;
03527                                 break;
03528                         }
03529                 }
03530                 if (foundIns) {
03531                         //printf("YAAY %d, ", ins->getInsID());
03532                         ins->setStatus(chain,-1,-1);
03533                         iResStations[indx]->Append(ins);
03534                         strand_formed = true;
03535                         total_num_strand_ins++;
03536                 } else {
03537                         break;
03538                 }
03539         } while (1);
03540         if (strand_formed) /* strand has a min length of 2 */
03541                 dyn_num_strands++;
03542 }
